Shipping with tracked delivery.About Caribbean Calcite:Caribbean Calcite brings serenity into your life. You won’t be able to take your eyes off these stunning blue tones. Tap into that third eye and crown chakra with these blue beauties, elevating your higher consciousness.It is a pretty new mineral that was found in 2019 in Pakistan. It’s a combination mineral of light green to blue calcite and brown, white or blue Aragonite. Although it is mined in Pakistan, this stone is called Caribbean Calcite due to the light aqua blue color, reminiscent of a pristine tropical beach. Caribbean blue Calcite is visually very captivating and able to transport you to an island paradise, reminiscing about dreamy beaches and the ocean. With its vibrant but calming colors, its energy uplifts and inspires. The stone is relatively soft and you will find crevices and surface imperfections, which give the stone even more character. It is a very popular and sought after stone and relatively rare, as it is only found in one spot in the world.

My Larimar is not enhanced or treated in any way.In these enchanting little moons, you can see the paradise ocean of the Caribbean sparkle!Find peace and clarity in the loving calmness of the Atlantis stone Larimar.About Larimar:Larimar is a very rare and precious member of the Pectolite family.It has only been found in one small location on the planet, a remote mountain range of the Dominican Republic in the Caribbean. The Larimar mines are considered Artisan mining since they rely mostly on human, physical labor. The mines are operated by a cooperative of local villages and they ensure that members of their local communities are the only ones mining. It is a major driver of community development, by providing jobs and ensuring profits for local villagers in the surrounding region.There are other names which have been applied to Larimar, for example “the Atlantis stone” and the “dolphin stone”.

name: Tarot resin art storage box "The Magician"
description: This box is made completely from epoxy resin. Into the lid a painted tarot card representing the magician is inlayed, and in the bottom of the box a painted skull is inlayed. The lid is transparent, meaning that you can see some of the inside the box when it is closed.Dimensions:Outer height with lid: 6.9cm (lid thickness: 1cm)Outer width: 9.5cmOuter length: 12.5cmInner height: 4cm without lid, 3.7cm with lidInner width: 7.5cmInner length: 10.5cmNotes on this item:The surface of the lid is even and smooth but there are some small irregularities on the edges of the surface. On the bottom of the lid (the side facing the inside of the box) there is one "bump" (visible in the last picture) where the surface is not even. This is where I filled a bubble in the casting!The bottom of the box (as can be seen in the last picture) is not completely regular. This is hardly noticeable when the box is the right way round and does not affect the inside.As with most resin cast objects there are a few small air bubbles on the surface of the box. These are mostly on the bottom edge and don't detract from the overall appearance.This is a completely handmade item, meaning that there may be some small imperfections - these add to the uniqueness of the product!Thank you so much for visiting my shop and for your interest in these items!
